# The Basics

First, you'll probably need to use a different operating system. The rest of this guide will assume you are on a **Linux** based system.

**Windows** has been known to spy on its users for a while now. There's an overwelming number of sources for this, but a good one is The PC Security Channel's "has windows become spyware?". It runs Windows 11's network activity on a clean installation on idle through wireshark. Check it out <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IT4vDfA_4NI" class="underline">here.</a>

**MacOS** and other Apple operating systems spy less, but still spy, despite Apple's advertising.

The following are the recommended Linux distros for daily usage:

